1
00:00:28,218 --> 00:00:36,901
THE FOLLOWING IS BASED
ON A TRUE STORY

2
00:00:39,918 --> 00:00:46,301
WALKÜRE

3
00:00:46,302 --> 00:00:52,901
VALKYRIE

4
00:00:55,347 --> 00:00:58,436
I swear by God this sacred oath:

5
00:00:58,437 --> 00:01:04,022
That I shall render unconditional
obedience to Adolf Hitler

6
00:01:04,023 --> 00:01:07,122
Führer of the German Reich and people,

7
00:01:07,123 --> 00:01:10,058
Supreme Commander
of the Armed Forces.

8
00:01:10,059 --> 00:01:13,323
And that I shall at all times be ready,
as a brave soldier,

9
00:01:13,324 --> 00:01:20,013
to give my life for this oath...

10
00:01:44,792 --> 00:01:50,398
The promises of the Führer about peace
and prosperity have been destroyed...

11
00:01:50,399 --> 00:01:55,411
and left nothing
but destruction.

12
00:01:56,646 --> 00:01:59,943
The pestilence
Hitler has brought with his SS,

13
00:01:59,944 --> 00:02:03,343
are shame and a disgrace
to the German army.

14
00:02:05,086 --> 00:02:09,747
In the Officers Choir
there is widespread disgust,

15
00:02:09,748 --> 00:02:14,332
about all the atrocities
committed by the Nazis.

16
00:02:14,333 --> 00:02:17,951
The killing of civilians,

17
00:02:17,952 --> 00:02:23,304
the torture and starvation
of prisoners,

18
00:02:23,305 --> 00:02:26,697
the mass execution of Jews.

19
00:02:26,850 --> 00:02:31,208
My duty as an Officer,
is no longer to save my country...

20
00:02:31,209 --> 00:02:34,553
but to save human lifes.

21
00:02:35,349 --> 00:02:36,722
I can not find one General...

22
00:02:36,723 --> 00:02:40,609
in the position to confront Hitler,
with the courage to do it.

23
00:02:40,610 --> 00:02:43,665
Colonel Stauffenberg, sir,
the General will be here in 4 hours.

24
00:02:43,666 --> 00:02:47,547
Thank you.
I need to see him, when he arrives.

25
00:02:51,431 --> 00:02:52,725
I found myself surrounded by men...

26
00:02:52,726 --> 00:02:55,885
unwilling... or unable...
to face the truth.

27
00:02:55,886 --> 00:02:59,490
Hitler is not only the arch enemy
of the entire world.

28
00:02:59,491 --> 00:03:02,784
but the arch-enemy of Germany.

29
00:03:03,477 --> 00:03:07,482
Change... must be made.

30
00:03:09,146 --> 00:03:12,092
Colonel, my orders are to advance
to Sidi Mansour and hold it.

31
00:03:12,093 --> 00:03:13,548
That what we'll do.

32
00:03:13,549 --> 00:03:16,261
The British are moving up from the south,
Patton is closing in on the coast,

33
00:03:16,262 --> 00:03:20,761
- you know we should've left 2 days ago.
- No, Colonel, we'll keep fighting...

34
00:03:20,762 --> 00:03:22,182
until the final victory.

35
00:03:22,183 --> 00:03:26,835
North Africa is lost, and you're gonna need
those men a year from now to defend Berlin.

36
00:03:26,836 --> 00:03:31,434
We can serve Germany,
or the Führer, not both.

37
00:03:32,317 --> 00:03:35,734
It's just that sort of talk,
that had you sent here, Colonel.

38
00:03:35,735 --> 00:03:39,272
What I said was much worse.

39
00:03:39,835 --> 00:03:42,563
General...

40
00:03:43,364 --> 00:03:46,955
I'm just trying to get these men
out of here alive.

41
00:03:53,542 --> 00:03:55,825
What would you have me do, huh?

42
00:03:55,826 --> 00:03:57,998
You tell headquarters we're low
on water, we have to re-route, so...

43
00:03:57,999 --> 00:04:03,594
we can join with the 21st Panzer's.
At least then we'll have a chance.

44
00:04:03,953 --> 00:04:06,005
And records will show
we didn't have enough water...

45
00:04:06,006 --> 00:04:10,884
- to reach Sidi Mansour?
- I can guarantee that.

46
00:04:19,586 --> 00:04:22,070
See that it's done.

47
00:04:22,071 --> 00:04:24,344
General.

48
00:07:54,823 --> 00:07:57,396
Up!

49
00:08:05,525 --> 00:08:07,511
Down!

50
00:08:24,178 --> 00:08:26,274
- Hurry, Hitler's leaving!
- Now?

51
00:08:26,275 --> 00:08:28,174
Yeah!
Let me set the fuse.

52
00:08:59,423 --> 00:09:01,520
Colonel Brandt!

53
00:09:01,523 --> 00:09:03,557
Colonel Brandt.

54
00:09:04,223 --> 00:09:07,158
My regards to Colonel Stief.

55
00:09:07,159 --> 00:09:09,342
Cointreau.

56
00:09:09,343 --> 00:09:13,275
Let's hope I don't get thirsty
on that flight.

57
00:09:36,158 --> 00:09:37,692
Tchekhov here.

58
00:09:45,292 --> 00:09:47,492
What happened?

59
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:51,622
He's landed.

60
00:09:58,479 --> 00:10:03,185
This is General Tchekhov... Connect me
with Operation's, Colonel Brandt.

61
00:10:05,153 --> 00:10:07,097
Colonel!
Tchekhov.

62
00:10:07,098 --> 00:10:09,019
I'm glad you arrived safely.

63
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:13,130
I hate to trouble you, but it seems you
have the wrong bottles for Colonel Stief.

64
00:10:14,252 --> 00:10:16,710
You do still have the package?

65
00:10:19,678 --> 00:10:23,365
Oh, no, as it happens I've been
called to Berlin unexpectedly.

66
00:10:23,366 --> 00:10:26,191
I can be at your office first thing
tomorrow morning to pick it up.

67
00:10:26,547 --> 00:10:29,929
Sorry for the inconvenience, Colonel.
Yes, thank you.

68
00:10:32,470 --> 00:10:34,489
Do you think he knows?

69
00:10:34,809 --> 00:10:37,298
There's only one way to find out.

70
00:10:49,601 --> 00:10:51,649
- We've been discovered.
- What makes you think that?

71
00:10:51,650 --> 00:10:53,831
Oster has been arrested.
The Gestapo came for him last night.

72
00:10:53,832 --> 00:10:56,723
The Gestapo could've arrested
him for anything.

73
00:10:56,787 --> 00:10:59,380
- What'd you think went wrong?
- We don't know.

74
00:10:59,381 --> 00:11:04,849
The fuse, the temperature, altitude,
the point is, the damn thing didn't go off.

75
00:11:14,132 --> 00:11:16,261
General Tchekhov to see
Colonel Brandt.

76
00:11:16,262 --> 00:11:19,182
The Colonel is expecting you, sir.

77
00:11:28,115 --> 00:11:30,521
At ease.

78
00:11:37,815 --> 00:11:39,101
Sit.

79
00:11:39,102 --> 00:11:40,550
You'll forgive me General,

80
00:11:40,551 --> 00:11:44,650
this little roundup is having me
writing reports... all day.

81
00:11:44,651 --> 00:11:47,650
- Roundup?
- Dissidenters.

82
00:11:48,151 --> 00:11:50,865
Another plot against the Führer.

83
00:11:50,866 --> 00:11:53,274
Who are these people?

84
00:11:55,334 --> 00:11:58,054
You'd be surprised.

85
00:12:02,257 --> 00:12:08,298
Is... this what you've come for?

86
00:12:12,638 --> 00:12:15,762
Perhaps we should... open it.

87
00:12:16,142 --> 00:12:17,808
I beg your pardon?

88
00:12:17,809 --> 00:12:23,609
Well, you've come a long way,
you must be... thirsty?

89
00:12:27,702 --> 00:12:30,006
You know, I wonder how the Führer,
who... does not partake,

90
00:12:30,007 --> 00:12:34,746
would feel about a soldier
who did so on... duty.

91
00:12:40,447 --> 00:12:42,768
Colonel Brandt.

92
00:12:44,353 --> 00:12:47,093
I took you for
an honest sort, General.

93
00:12:48,570 --> 00:12:51,403
And I, you.

94
00:12:58,714 --> 00:13:00,828
We are still in business.

95
00:13:01,446 --> 00:13:03,197
Find a replacement for Oster.

96
00:13:03,198 --> 00:13:06,053
There's no one we can trust,
not in Berlin.

97
00:13:06,154 --> 00:13:08,619
Then stop looking in Berlin.

98
00:13:34,051 --> 00:13:36,531
Frau von Stauffenberg?

99
00:13:36,981 --> 00:13:39,774
Perhaps, before you go in, we could
have a word together in my office.

100
00:13:39,775 --> 00:13:42,064
I will see my husband now.

101
00:13:49,345 --> 00:13:52,451
His right hand has been
amputated above the wrist.

102
00:13:52,452 --> 00:13:55,619
He's missing the 4th and
5th fingers on the left hand.

103
00:13:56,004 --> 00:13:58,584
We... couldn't save the left eye.

104
00:14:54,558 --> 00:14:56,974
Colonel?

105
00:14:58,180 --> 00:14:59,887
Are you ready, sir?

106
00:15:39,607 --> 00:15:42,966
I'm a soldier, I serve my country.

107
00:15:44,012 --> 00:15:46,115
But this is not my country.

108
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:49,036
When I was lying there,
bleeding to death, thinking:

109
00:15:49,037 --> 00:15:54,822
If I die now, I leave nothing
to my children, but shame.

110
00:15:57,134 --> 00:16:01,385
I know now there's only
one way to serve Germany.

111
00:16:01,653 --> 00:16:04,174
And in doing so,
I'll be a traitor.

112
00:16:04,594 --> 00:16:06,649
I accept that.

113
00:16:06,990 --> 00:16:10,798
Just tell me,
can these men see it through?

114
00:16:12,718 --> 00:16:16,073
We need to reorganize,
reconsider our strategy...

115
00:16:16,074 --> 00:16:18,412
and recruit new men.

116
00:16:18,413 --> 00:16:21,297
That's why we want you.

117
00:16:23,124 --> 00:16:25,646
You understand what will happen
to my wife and children...

118
00:16:25,647 --> 00:16:29,146
if these men can't see it through?

119
00:16:31,607 --> 00:16:34,828
Come and hear what
they have to say.

120
00:16:46,672 --> 00:16:49,104
You know where to find us.

121
00:17:14,061 --> 00:17:16,587
It's enough! Enough!

122
00:17:16,588 --> 00:17:19,705
I'm not gonna listen to another word
of this, you had your chance, you failed.

123
00:17:19,706 --> 00:17:23,763
Your so-called simple solution
didn't work.

124
00:17:23,764 --> 00:17:26,354
Our only option now
is to confront Hilter openly...

125
00:17:26,355 --> 00:17:27,860
This is a military operation.

126
00:17:27,861 --> 00:17:30,266
It's not a military operation!
It's a political organization,

127
00:17:30,267 --> 00:17:33,252
and one that's given it's
military-arm too much control...

128
00:17:33,253 --> 00:17:35,364
In any military exercise, you have to
expect a certain measure of deviation.

129
00:17:35,365 --> 00:17:39,122
A measure? A measure? What about...
total, complete, utter failure?

130
00:17:39,123 --> 00:17:41,906
Gentlemen, I think it's time
we face the fact...

131
00:17:41,907 --> 00:17:45,506
the allies are coming,
sooner or later, I say, we sit back...

132
00:17:45,507 --> 00:17:47,154
and let them wipe out the Nazis.

133
00:17:47,155 --> 00:17:50,658
And ask every living soul in Europe
to pay the price? Use your head.

134
00:17:50,659 --> 00:17:51,742
Karl, please!

135
00:17:51,743 --> 00:17:54,224
I'm sorry, Ludwig.
I've held my tounge too long.

136
00:17:54,225 --> 00:17:56,427
We must confront Hitler now.

137
00:17:56,428 --> 00:17:57,598
Force him out!

138
00:17:57,599 --> 00:17:59,235
And then what?

139
00:18:00,597 --> 00:18:02,092
I beg your pardon?

140
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:05,368
When Hilter is gone, then what?

141
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:09,767
I'm sorry, who is this man?

142
00:18:09,768 --> 00:18:12,411
Colonel Stauffenberg
is Oster's replacement.

143
00:18:12,412 --> 00:18:15,991
He's been transferred to my office,
at the War Ministry.

144
00:18:16,577 --> 00:18:18,374
How is your uncle?

145
00:18:18,375 --> 00:18:20,145
He's well, sir.
He sends his regards.

146
00:18:20,146 --> 00:18:21,671
He speaks very highly of you.

147
00:18:21,672 --> 00:18:23,538
And of you, General.

148
00:18:23,539 --> 00:18:26,106
There was one thing that made
Oster such a great organizer,

149
00:18:26,107 --> 00:18:29,591
he kept his opinions
to himself.

150
00:18:30,125 --> 00:18:33,809
I'm simply asking what you intend
to do when Hitler is gone.

151
00:18:33,810 --> 00:18:36,356
You don't really believe you can
just walk into the Reich-chancellery,

152
00:18:36,357 --> 00:18:38,956
and command the army
to end the war?

153
00:18:38,957 --> 00:18:41,573
Yes, we do.

154
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:49,178
You're in the presence of men who
could have been Hitler's inner circle.

155
00:18:49,179 --> 00:18:52,267
Instead, we refused, Colonel.

156
00:18:52,328 --> 00:18:55,981
The people know we put our principles
above personal gain.

157
00:18:55,982 --> 00:18:57,905
We have the respect of the people...

158
00:18:57,906 --> 00:19:00,346
and the army.

159
00:19:01,627 --> 00:19:03,940
Then you don't need me.

160
00:19:05,409 --> 00:19:07,279
Gentlemen.

161
00:19:09,473 --> 00:19:12,495
Those men are confusing
respect with popularity.

162
00:19:12,496 --> 00:19:14,478
The Army swore an oath,

163
00:19:14,479 --> 00:19:17,178
an oath that won't just die...
with Hitler.

164
00:19:17,179 --> 00:19:18,472
What 're you gonna do?

165
00:19:18,473 --> 00:19:20,573
How will you deal with Göbbels,
Himmler and the SS?

166
00:19:20,574 --> 00:19:23,350
- They will wipe you out!
- It doesn't matter!

167
00:19:25,673 --> 00:19:30,009
It only matters that we act, now,
before we lose the war.

168
00:19:30,027 --> 00:19:34,239
Otherwise, this will always
be Hitler's Germany,

169
00:19:36,290 --> 00:19:40,542
And we have to show the world...
not all of us were like him.

170
00:19:40,543 --> 00:19:43,819
That's not enough for me.

171
00:19:44,078 --> 00:19:47,272
There has to be
a chance of success.

172
00:19:47,749 --> 00:19:49,552
Then find a way.

173
00:19:49,941 --> 00:19:52,549
- Papi! Papi!
- Papi is home!

174
00:19:52,550 --> 00:19:53,997
- Papi!
- Papi!

175
00:19:53,998 --> 00:19:55,002
- Papi is home!
- Papi!

176
00:19:55,003 --> 00:20:00,150
- Papi, Papi!
- Papi is here!

177
00:20:08,633 --> 00:20:11,981
I thought we agreed...
I'd come see you in Bamberg.

178
00:20:11,998 --> 00:20:14,000
The children couldn't wait.

179
00:20:14,276 --> 00:20:15,929
The children?

180
00:22:37,982 --> 00:22:40,598
Valkyrie.

181
00:22:40,599 --> 00:22:42,235
We've already considered Valkyrie,
it isn't suitable...

182
00:22:42,236 --> 00:22:43,535
Not as it is currently written...

183
00:22:43,536 --> 00:22:45,617
but the Colonel has an idea
I think we should consider.

184
00:22:45,618 --> 00:22:47,077
Excuse me, what is Valkyrie?

185
00:22:47,078 --> 00:22:48,775
Operation Valkyrie.

186
00:22:48,776 --> 00:22:51,872
The reserve army has
thousands of men, all over Berlin.

187
00:22:51,873 --> 00:22:55,804
Valkyrie is... Hitler's contingency plan
to mobilize those men...

188
00:22:55,805 --> 00:22:57,278
during a national emergency.

189
00:22:57,279 --> 00:22:59,394
The sole purpose of the order is
to protect Hitler's government...

190
00:22:59,395 --> 00:23:02,359
- if he's cut-off or killed.
- And... what use is this to us?

191
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:05,585
Valkyrie is designed
to contain... civil unrest.

192
00:23:05,668 --> 00:23:09,539
But what if the S.S.
were staging a coup?

193
00:23:12,664 --> 00:23:15,125
State Security is trying
to overthrow Hitler...

194
00:23:15,126 --> 00:23:17,096
How would High Command respond?

195
00:23:17,097 --> 00:23:19,020
We would have no choice... but to
declare a military state of emergency.

196
00:23:19,021 --> 00:23:21,120
Exactly... and initiate Valkyrie.

197
00:23:21,121 --> 00:23:23,740
Hitler's own reserve army
using Hitler's own plan.

198
00:23:23,741 --> 00:23:26,520
We'll have no choice
but to cease power in Berlin,

199
00:23:26,521 --> 00:23:30,032
to prevent the SS take-over.

200
00:23:30,033 --> 00:23:33,196
They'll think they're fighting for
Hilter's government, not against it.

201
00:23:33,197 --> 00:23:37,373
While we quietly put
a new government in place.

202
00:23:37,374 --> 00:23:40,098
But only if he's dead.

203
00:23:40,655 --> 00:23:42,227
That's what you're saying, isn't it?

204
00:23:42,228 --> 00:23:45,742
How else you're gonna convince people
the SS is trying to seize power?

205
00:23:45,743 --> 00:23:48,504
- We have to kill Hitler.
- I'm disappointed in you, Colonel.

206
00:23:48,505 --> 00:23:50,894
I thought a man
of your background...

207
00:23:50,895 --> 00:23:53,194
would suggest a more
honorable approach.

208
00:23:53,195 --> 00:23:57,026
Your plan has a few
minor obstacles, Colonel.

209
00:23:57,027 --> 00:24:00,559
Firstly, Valkyrie would have to be
rewritten to exclude the SS!

210
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:03,958
And I'll need your help
to get a copy.

211
00:24:03,959 --> 00:24:06,370
Rewriting an order is one thing.

212
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:09,892
Distributing it, is another.

213
00:24:09,893 --> 00:24:14,888
In this case we'd be willfully circulating
written evidence of high treason.

214
00:24:14,889 --> 00:24:17,543
Evidence requiring Hitler's signature.

215
00:24:22,767 --> 00:24:25,547
Well, we can all draw straws
for the job.

216
00:24:26,594 --> 00:24:29,009
- And what about Fromm?
- Fromm? Who is Fromm?

217
00:24:29,010 --> 00:24:30,545
He's the commander
of the reserve army.

218
00:24:30,546 --> 00:24:35,153
I can put the reserve troops on alert,
but only Fromm can initiate Valkyrie.

219
00:24:37,844 --> 00:24:39,550
Can you get to him?

220
00:24:40,951 --> 00:24:42,840
I don't know.

221
00:24:42,841 --> 00:24:45,641
We're running out of time.
Can you get to Fromm?

222
00:24:45,642 --> 00:24:47,224
He is a careerist pig.

223
00:24:47,225 --> 00:24:49,769
But one who has gone as far
as he can go in Hitler's army.

224
00:24:49,770 --> 00:24:51,708
It's no secret
he's not happy about it.

225
00:24:51,709 --> 00:24:54,448
Offer him a key position
in the new regime.

226
00:24:54,886 --> 00:24:57,551
Make him see the light.

227
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:07,516
You have to put it in there.

228
00:25:11,034 --> 00:25:13,094
Colonel Stauffenberg
for General Fromm.

229
00:25:13,095 --> 00:25:15,803
Colonel Stauffenberg, sir.
Welcome back to the War Ministry.

230
00:25:15,804 --> 00:25:17,845
It's an honor, sir.

231
00:25:18,938 --> 00:25:21,534
I'd send you to the front,
but I think you'd surrender...

232
00:25:21,535 --> 00:25:24,604
just to be Montgomery's whore!

233
00:25:29,557 --> 00:25:31,518
The General will see you now.

234
00:25:45,403 --> 00:25:47,643
What is it you want?

235
00:25:47,744 --> 00:25:52,674
I wanted to introduce our new man,
Colonel Stauffenberg.

236
00:25:53,131 --> 00:25:55,716
Ah! From Africa!

237
00:25:55,783 --> 00:26:00,537
Well, I... I'd offer you my hand,
but I... I might not get it back.

238
00:26:00,538 --> 00:26:04,471
I'd say the General has lost more
important things this morning.

239
00:26:11,090 --> 00:26:13,513
It's about time they put somebody
with balls into this office.

240
00:26:13,514 --> 00:26:15,356
Please sit down, Colonel.

241
00:26:15,357 --> 00:26:18,358
And you, Olbricht, if you must.

242
00:26:29,555 --> 00:26:31,955
They tell me
you're critical of the war, Colonel.

243
00:26:31,956 --> 00:26:34,555
Not that you don't...
seem to have good reasons.

244
00:26:34,556 --> 00:26:36,622
I'm critical of indecision, General.

245
00:26:36,623 --> 00:26:39,256
- In the field?
- In Berlin.

246
00:26:40,942 --> 00:26:45,009
So, that's why you're here I take it,
to... huh, to make decisions.

247
00:26:45,010 --> 00:26:46,714
I've already made my decision.

248
00:26:46,715 --> 00:26:49,693
I'm here to help others
make theirs.

249
00:26:53,671 --> 00:26:56,356
They say
when there's no clear option...

250
00:26:56,757 --> 00:26:58,556
the best thing is... to do nothing.

251
00:26:58,557 --> 00:27:01,932
We're at war... we must act.

252
00:27:01,933 --> 00:27:04,738
Sometimes... rushing.

253
00:27:05,604 --> 00:27:09,397
And what rash action
did you have in mind, Colonel?

254
00:27:10,461 --> 00:27:15,760
That would be a decision for the
supreme military commander... Sir.

255
00:27:15,761 --> 00:27:18,993
A supreme... commander?

256
00:27:20,409 --> 00:27:23,338
Second only to the Chancellor.

257
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:35,461
If I were that man... this war
would be going quite differently.

258
00:27:35,462 --> 00:27:38,584
Well, we were thinking
the same thing, really.

259
00:27:46,263 --> 00:27:54,668
I don't need to remind you...
that we've all sworn an oath...

260
00:27:54,833 --> 00:27:57,405
to the Führer.

261
00:28:01,504 --> 00:28:03,871
And...

262
00:28:04,504 --> 00:28:07,572
Having said that, I'm gonna forget
this conversation ever took place.

263
00:28:07,573 --> 00:28:10,581
In the strict understanding
that such talk never occurs again...

264
00:28:10,582 --> 00:28:12,588
- under this roof. Is that clear?
- Yes, sir.

265
00:28:12,589 --> 00:28:13,665
Yes, sir.

266
00:28:13,666 --> 00:28:17,456
You can tell your friends, Colonel,
that I always come down on the right side.

267
00:28:17,457 --> 00:28:23,801
And as long as the Führer is alive,
you know what side that is.

268
00:28:30,241 --> 00:28:31,549
Heil, Hitler.

269
00:28:31,550 --> 00:28:33,724
- Heil, Hitler.
- Heil, Hitler.

270
00:29:30,015 --> 00:29:32,613
Do you realize
how close I am to Hitler?

271
00:29:32,926 --> 00:29:36,334
With one word,
I can make you disappear.

272
00:29:36,639 --> 00:29:39,063
My associates don't know we've been
talking, if that's what you're afraid of.

273
00:29:39,064 --> 00:29:43,360
When the SS catch you, they will
pull you apart, like warm bread.

274
00:29:43,361 --> 00:29:46,606
It would be a crime
just to have known you then.

275
00:29:46,719 --> 00:29:49,468
I warn you,
don't you try to contact me again.

276
00:29:49,469 --> 00:29:51,311
You won't report me.

277
00:29:51,312 --> 00:29:54,066
Maybe if you'd had,
when I first approached you,

278
00:29:54,067 --> 00:29:57,292
you might've been
keeping your oath then.

279
00:29:57,293 --> 00:29:58,980
Now you're just as guilty
as we are.

280
00:29:58,981 --> 00:30:00,655
And I guess that makes me
a sympathizer, hey?

281
00:30:00,656 --> 00:30:03,671
Give a man a choice to betray
his fellow officer's or his Führer,

282
00:30:03,672 --> 00:30:06,046
and you think his action
will show you his heart?

283
00:30:06,047 --> 00:30:08,776
- It is not that simple.
- Yes... It is.

284
00:30:08,777 --> 00:30:12,513
For the last time,
don't push me to make a decision.

285
00:30:12,514 --> 00:30:15,429
I don't have a choice.
It's clear now.

286
00:30:16,902 --> 00:30:20,329
Without you,
there is no hope of success.

287
00:30:20,515 --> 00:30:22,850
You're nothing but rats,
jumping from a sinking ship!

288
00:30:22,851 --> 00:30:25,231
What makes you think
you'll be any different?

289
00:30:25,232 --> 00:30:27,046
What makes you think
you're stronger than the people?

290
00:30:27,047 --> 00:30:29,325
The Reich?
The very momentum of history?

291
00:30:29,326 --> 00:30:31,893
This is going to happen.
Action is inevitable...

292
00:30:31,894 --> 00:30:33,555
as are the consequences.

293
00:30:33,556 --> 00:30:35,822
When they'll come for me,
I'll do everything I can, to hide...

294
00:30:35,823 --> 00:30:38,234
what you are doing...
but don't delude yourself...

295
00:30:38,235 --> 00:30:43,274
you were invloved in a crime against
your country long before you met me.

296
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:48,077
And there may still be time
to redeem yourself.

297
00:30:51,039 --> 00:30:54,428
Only God can judge us now.

298
00:30:59,625 --> 00:31:01,342
Hitler had
Operation Valkyrie designed...

299
00:31:01,343 --> 00:31:04,042
to completely secure
his government in 6 hours.

300
00:31:04,043 --> 00:31:08,679
I'm rewriting the order so we can
seize control of the government in 3.

301
00:31:08,698 --> 00:31:10,619
As written, the orders
spreads reserve troops across...

302
00:31:10,620 --> 00:31:12,751
all of Germany's 19 military districts,

303
00:31:12,752 --> 00:31:17,058
including occupied cities
like Paris, Vienna and Prague.

304
00:31:17,059 --> 00:31:19,294
This is a waste of resources,
since all these districts...

305
00:31:19,295 --> 00:31:22,221
follow orders from Berlin
without question.

306
00:31:22,222 --> 00:31:25,868
If you take Berlin,
you take Germany.

307
00:31:25,869 --> 00:31:27,331
I'm rewriting Valkyrie...

308
00:31:27,332 --> 00:31:32,431
to direct the majority of our strongest
units to focus entirely on Berlin.

309
00:31:32,458 --> 00:31:35,846
We'll surround the government quarter,
occupy all SS and police barracks.

310
00:31:35,847 --> 00:31:37,443
Once we have control
of the government,

311
00:31:37,444 --> 00:31:40,330
we'll shut down
all concentration camps.

312
00:31:40,331 --> 00:31:42,861
Any officers who resist
will be arrested.

313
00:31:42,862 --> 00:31:45,740
I've been transferred to the front.

314
00:31:47,909 --> 00:31:52,096
Anyway, it doesn't matter...
you know these orders better than anyone.

315
00:31:52,199 --> 00:31:55,790
That's why I'm putting you in charge
of the military wing of the operation.

316
00:31:55,791 --> 00:31:58,568
- Beck agrees.
- Why not Olbricht?

317
00:31:58,569 --> 00:32:00,906
No, it's your plan.

318
00:32:00,907 --> 00:32:03,416
It's you.
And one more thing...

319
00:32:03,417 --> 00:32:04,861
you need to be absolutely certain...

320
00:32:04,862 --> 00:32:06,861
no conflicting orders
get out after the flash.

321
00:32:06,862 --> 00:32:09,088
It is not enough to kill Hitler.

322
00:32:09,089 --> 00:32:11,047
You need to isolate
his chain of command...

323
00:32:11,048 --> 00:32:13,547
and cut them off from
the outside world immediately.

324
00:32:13,548 --> 00:32:16,289
Yes, I already
considered that.

325
00:32:16,290 --> 00:32:18,077
I think I have just the man
who can help.

326
00:32:18,078 --> 00:32:20,006
Who is he?

327
00:32:20,088 --> 00:32:23,313
Perhaps it's better if I didn't say.

328
00:32:26,399 --> 00:32:29,298
You know, God promised Abraham
he would not destroy Sodom...

329
00:32:29,299 --> 00:32:32,098
if he could find just
10 righteous men.

330
00:32:32,099 --> 00:32:37,079
I have a feeling that for Germany,
it may come down to one.

331
00:32:42,241 --> 00:32:44,132
Let's begin.

332
00:32:44,133 --> 00:32:46,632
The Führer...

333
00:32:48,833 --> 00:32:51,132
Adolf Hitler...

334
00:32:51,133 --> 00:32:53,432
is dead.

335
00:32:58,072 --> 00:33:00,792
Heil Hitler, General.

336
00:33:03,270 --> 00:33:06,323
Would you excuse us?

337
00:33:12,428 --> 00:33:15,186
You play the part
of bureaucrat beautifully.

338
00:33:15,187 --> 00:33:17,934
Well, I don't feel like
I get to relax.

339
00:33:17,935 --> 00:33:21,764
You've been promoted chief of staff
for the reserve army.

340
00:33:22,265 --> 00:33:25,533
- Excuse me?
- Congratulations.

341
00:33:26,052 --> 00:33:28,557
I am busy with other things.

342
00:33:28,558 --> 00:33:32,587
Unfortunately, your nocturnal activities
don't count as service to the 'Reich'.

343
00:33:32,588 --> 00:33:35,569
- I'll refuse the promotion.
- You'll do no such thing.

344
00:33:36,249 --> 00:33:38,011
Tchekhov may have left you
in charge of the operation...

345
00:33:38,012 --> 00:33:40,194
but in this world I still outrank you.

346
00:33:40,195 --> 00:33:42,231
You will accept the promotion.

347
00:33:42,232 --> 00:33:46,252
You'll have real access to Hitler,
his advisers, his schedule.

348
00:33:46,253 --> 00:33:49,124
We need this.

349
00:33:49,678 --> 00:33:53,328
I've looked through
your changes to Valkyrie.

350
00:33:53,733 --> 00:33:58,492
I approve.
I need you to get Hitler to sign it.

351
00:34:01,184 --> 00:34:04,490
Now, there's a man here
to interview as your adjudant.

352
00:34:04,491 --> 00:34:07,461
He comes highly recommended.

353
00:34:12,959 --> 00:34:15,574
Close the door.

354
00:34:18,551 --> 00:34:20,812
Be seated.

355
00:34:23,592 --> 00:34:26,624
Do you know how
this world will end, Lieutenant?

356
00:34:26,625 --> 00:34:33,295
The portrait will be unhung,
and that man will be hung.

357
00:34:39,659 --> 00:34:43,121
I'm engaged in high treason
with all means available to me.

358
00:34:43,122 --> 00:34:45,558
Can I count you in?

359
00:34:51,750 --> 00:34:55,901
For anything, sir.
Anything at all.

360
00:35:52,370 --> 00:35:55,367
Come.
Come Stephan.

361
00:35:55,770 --> 00:35:57,767
Pappa is real busy.

362
00:36:01,770 --> 00:36:03,659
Colonel Brandt, operations.

363
00:36:03,660 --> 00:36:08,245
Colonel Stauffenberg, I'd like to review
your presentation to the Führer.

364
00:36:08,268 --> 00:36:10,039
Strictly routine.

365
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:12,442
Sir, the contents of the Colonel's
bag are for the Führer's eyes only.

366
00:36:12,443 --> 00:36:14,429
I'm the Führer's eyes, Lieutenant.

367
00:36:14,430 --> 00:36:16,572
The Colonel is a member
of my staff at the War Ministry.

368
00:36:16,573 --> 00:36:19,231
He doesn't answer to you.

369
00:36:20,162 --> 00:36:22,540
They're waiting.

370
00:36:22,643 --> 00:36:24,903
This way.

371
00:36:58,616 --> 00:37:01,433
My Führer!... May I present
Colonel Stauffenberg,

372
00:37:01,434 --> 00:37:04,133
our new chief of staff
in the reserve army.

373
00:37:04,134 --> 00:37:06,474
Heil, my Führer.

374
00:37:11,570 --> 00:37:15,773
I can't tell you, what an honor
this is to meet an officer who has...

375
00:37:15,774 --> 00:37:20,073
sacrificed so much for Germany.

376
00:37:24,866 --> 00:37:28,347
If only more of my men
were like you.

377
00:37:29,156 --> 00:37:31,253
Let this man stand as an example
for all of you here.

378
00:37:31,254 --> 00:37:34,953
He is the ideal
German... Officer.

379
00:37:36,123 --> 00:37:38,997
My Führer...
Colonel Stauffenberg...

380
00:37:38,998 --> 00:37:41,623
was asked to come here today
to brief us on mobilizing...

381
00:37:41,624 --> 00:37:46,517
Troops of the reserve army,
to... to repell the invasion.

382
00:37:47,428 --> 00:37:49,402
Invasion?

383
00:37:49,739 --> 00:37:51,138
At...

384
00:37:51,139 --> 00:37:53,563
Normandy, my Führer.

385
00:37:54,317 --> 00:37:57,056
Oh, yes.

386
00:37:57,276 --> 00:38:00,010
Normandy.

387
00:38:00,073 --> 00:38:02,884
That will not be necessary.

388
00:38:03,026 --> 00:38:08,634
Reichsmarshall Göring assures me
that everything is completely under control.

389
00:38:10,272 --> 00:38:12,611
Thank you, Colonel.

390
00:38:15,813 --> 00:38:18,668
My Führer, if I may...
I have an amended copy...

391
00:38:18,669 --> 00:38:22,291
of Operation Valkyrie,
for your approval.

392
00:39:11,196 --> 00:39:15,153
You know your Wagner, Colonel?

393
00:39:19,603 --> 00:39:23,955
The Valkyrie,
handmaidens of the gods.

394
00:39:23,956 --> 00:39:26,869
Choosing who will live
and who will die.

395
00:39:26,870 --> 00:39:29,980
Sparing the most heroic...

396
00:39:29,981 --> 00:39:33,580
from an agonizing death.

397
00:39:37,661 --> 00:39:41,693
One cannot understand
National-Socialism...

398
00:39:42,426 --> 00:39:45,750
if one does not
understand Wagner.

399
00:40:00,345 --> 00:40:05,007
I'm sure whatever changes
you've made are for the best.

400
00:40:08,457 --> 00:40:11,131
You' re dismissed.
Send your man home. And Fromm!

401
00:40:11,132 --> 00:40:15,573
Have some fresh tea
brought in, will you?

402
00:40:26,258 --> 00:40:28,090
I don't know
what you're brewin' now.

403
00:40:28,091 --> 00:40:29,919
And I don't wanna know.

404
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:31,558
But when the music stops,

405
00:40:31,559 --> 00:40:36,158
I'd be obliged if Keitel
found himself without a chair.

406
00:40:47,736 --> 00:40:49,922
Any problem on earth
can be solved...

407
00:40:49,923 --> 00:40:53,227
with the careful application
of high-explosives.

408
00:40:53,228 --> 00:40:56,570
The of trick is not to be around
when they go off.

409
00:40:56,571 --> 00:41:00,134
Two 975 gram packs of plastic
explosives, enough explosive...

410
00:41:00,135 --> 00:41:02,004
to cripple a Panzer.

411
00:41:02,005 --> 00:41:04,328
Your detonators, your fuses.

412
00:41:04,329 --> 00:41:06,147
British time pencils.

413
00:41:06,148 --> 00:41:08,317
This acid capsule is your trigger.

414
00:41:08,318 --> 00:41:09,648
When you're ready to to arm...

415
00:41:09,649 --> 00:41:12,548
attach the detonator
to the bottom of the time pencil.

416
00:41:12,549 --> 00:41:14,044
Like so.

417
00:41:14,045 --> 00:41:17,965
Insert the entire device into
either end of the plastic "W".

418
00:41:17,966 --> 00:41:21,004
Crush the acid capsule...

419
00:41:21,005 --> 00:41:23,586
and you're live.

420
00:41:23,587 --> 00:41:28,253
When the acid eats through the wire
holding back the firing pin, well...

421
00:41:28,254 --> 00:41:31,253
you'll wanna be very far away.

422
00:41:33,479 --> 00:41:36,750
- For you.
- How much time do we have?

423
00:41:36,751 --> 00:41:39,249
Theoretically there's a 30 minute
delay, but with the kind of heat...

424
00:41:39,250 --> 00:41:42,832
you can expect at the Wolf's Lair,
I give you 10, 15 minutes, tops.

425
00:41:42,833 --> 00:41:44,784
That's hardly precise.

426
00:41:44,785 --> 00:41:48,525
This is state-of-the-art. You can
have small or precise, not both.

427
00:41:48,526 --> 00:41:51,279
- Might this just be a little too small?
- No.

428
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:53,527
Hitler bunker
will magnify the blast.

429
00:41:53,528 --> 00:41:57,347
It's constructed of reinforced concrete,
with steel doors, no windows.

430
00:41:57,348 --> 00:42:01,048
The air-pressure generated by just one
of these explosives in a space like that...

431
00:42:01,049 --> 00:42:04,948
Will kill everyone, instantly, the 2nd
charge will be entirely redundant.

432
00:42:04,949 --> 00:42:08,467
If, by some miracle,
Hiltler does survive, what then?

433
00:42:08,468 --> 00:42:10,533
We sitll initiate Valkyrie.

434
00:42:10,534 --> 00:42:13,433
At that point
there'll be no turning back.

435
00:42:13,434 --> 00:42:15,912
But we'll have an advantage.

436
00:42:16,413 --> 00:42:19,046
We have an inside man
at the Wolf's Lair.

437
00:42:19,047 --> 00:42:21,760
After the flash he'll cut off
communication with the outside world.

438
00:42:21,761 --> 00:42:24,004
While Hitler's inner-circle
is struggling to regroup...

439
00:42:24,005 --> 00:42:28,152
We'll have the momentum
we need to seize control in Berlin.

440
00:42:28,153 --> 00:42:31,859
Himmler is expected to be at
the meeting as well. Don't proceed...

441
00:42:31,860 --> 00:42:35,032
- unless you can get them both.
- What?

442
00:42:35,033 --> 00:42:39,934
Don't proceed unless you're confident
you can get both Himmler and Hitler.

443
00:42:45,481 --> 00:42:48,443
This is Gördeler, isn't it?

444
00:42:51,197 --> 00:42:52,832
Yeah, I'll hold off.

445
00:42:52,833 --> 00:42:54,265
If the decision is unanimous.

446
00:42:54,266 --> 00:42:56,813
But I want another man
on the committee.

447
00:42:56,814 --> 00:42:59,451
- Not a politician.
- Who?

448
00:42:59,452 --> 00:43:02,786
- Him.
- Him?

449
00:43:03,678 --> 00:43:07,678
- Fine.
- But remember...

450
00:43:07,679 --> 00:43:10,163
this is a military operation.

451
00:43:10,164 --> 00:43:13,566
Nothing ever goes
according to plan.

452
00:43:40,879 --> 00:43:44,636
I'll take the children to Bamberg.

453
00:43:50,131 --> 00:43:52,391
If I fail...

454
00:43:55,095 --> 00:43:57,334
They'll come for you.

455
00:43:58,301 --> 00:44:00,597
All of you.

456
00:44:03,302 --> 00:44:05,641
I know.

457
00:44:30,778 --> 00:44:32,554
Gentlemen, good morning.

458
00:44:32,555 --> 00:44:36,125
Hitler has scheduled a military briefing
for today, at one o'clock.

459
00:44:36,126 --> 00:44:38,487
Stauffenberg will start
once everyone is present.

460
00:44:38,488 --> 00:44:39,860
They're here.

461
00:44:39,861 --> 00:44:44,540
Before arming the explosives, Stauffenberg
will call for authorization to proceed.

462
00:44:44,541 --> 00:44:49,126
After the flash, his inside man
wil sever all communication.

463
00:44:49,188 --> 00:44:52,767
Assuming Fromm refuses to join us,
Olbricht will take command...

464
00:44:52,768 --> 00:44:55,524
of the reserve army
and initiate Valkyrie.

465
00:44:55,525 --> 00:44:57,153
Then you'll notify
all district commanders...

466
00:44:57,154 --> 00:44:59,996
that the SS is attempting
to seize power.

467
00:44:59,997 --> 00:45:04,293
The reserve army will arrest all SS,
Gestapo and Nazi officials.

468
00:45:04,294 --> 00:45:06,373
By then Stauffenberg
will have returned to Berlin...

469
00:45:06,374 --> 00:45:08,897
and taken command
of the reserve army.

470
00:45:08,898 --> 00:45:12,101
Witzleben and I will assume the role
of commander of the armed forces,

471
00:45:12,102 --> 00:45:14,141
and are head of state.

472
00:45:14,142 --> 00:45:16,726
With Berlin secured, Dr. Gördeler
will address the nation...

473
00:45:16,727 --> 00:45:18,664
as our new Chancellor.

474
00:45:18,665 --> 00:45:23,082
Then, God willing, we can negotiate
a truce with the allies.

475
00:45:23,083 --> 00:45:26,734
Save Europe
from total destruction.

476
00:45:27,645 --> 00:45:30,623
This will identify you
as a member of the operation,

477
00:45:30,624 --> 00:45:35,003
Nobody goes in or out
of the parimeter without one.

478
00:45:35,247 --> 00:45:37,169
Gentlemen.

479
00:45:37,170 --> 00:45:40,554
This is the most important day
of your lives.

480
00:45:42,112 --> 00:45:44,990
Long live sacred Germany.

481
00:46:20,060 --> 00:46:21,861
- Captain.
- What is it?

482
00:46:21,862 --> 00:46:23,442
An order
from General Olbricht's office.

483
00:46:23,443 --> 00:46:26,110
He is calling the reserve army
for some sort of standby action...

484
00:46:26,111 --> 00:46:29,386
in all the military districts,
including Berlin.

485
00:46:29,494 --> 00:46:33,462
Looks like a drill of some kind.
Send it through, Sergeant.

486
00:46:51,308 --> 00:46:53,620
Sir?

487
00:46:58,205 --> 00:47:01,552
Standby action,
what the hell for?

488
00:47:01,553 --> 00:47:03,779
The order doesn't say.

489
00:47:04,103 --> 00:47:06,053
Assemble the men.

490
